codes.0: Name entered under forename or in direct order
codes.1: Name entered under surname (family name, patronymic etc.)

2.label: has System code in Personal name used as subject
2.description: The system or thesaurus from which the subject heading is derived.

3.label: has Authority record number in Personal name used as subject

a.label: has Entry element in Personal name used as subject
a.description: The portion of the name used as the entry element in the heading.

b.label: has Part of name other than entry element in Personal name used as subject
b.description: The remainder of the name, used when the entry element is a surname or family name.

c.label: has Additions to name other than dates in Personal name used as subject
c.description: Any additions to names (other than dates) which do not form an integral part of the name itself.

d.label: has Roman numerals in Personal name used as subject
d.description: Roman numerals associated with names of certain popes, royalty and ecclesiastics.

f.label: has Dates in Personal name used as subject
f.description: The dates attached to personal names together with abbreviations or other indications of the nature of the dates.

g.label: has Expansion of initials of forename in Personal name used as subject
g.description: The full form of forenames when initials are recorded in Part of Name Other than Entry Element.

j.label: has Form subdivision in Personal name used as subject
j.description: A term added to the subject heading to further specify the kind(s) or genre(s) of material.

p.label: has Affiliation/address in Personal name used as subject
p.description: The institutional affiliation of the individual at the time the work was prepared.

t.label: has Title in Personal name used as subject

x.label: has Topical subdivision in Personal name used as subject
x.description: A term added to the subject heading to further specify the kind(s) or genre(s) of material.

y.label: has Geographical subdivision in Personal name used as subject
y.description: A term added to a subject heading to specify a place in relation to a person which the subject heading represents.

z.label: has Chronological subdivision in Personal name used as subject
z.description: A term added to a subject heading to specify the period in time in relation to a person whom the subject heading represents.

k.description: The date of publication of the item as subject when it is necessary to add it to the uniform title to distinguish the item.

l.label: has Form subheading in Title used as subject
l.description: A standard phrase added to a heading to further specify the uniform title.

s.description: A number assigned by the composer or others to distinguish works.

u.label: has Key (for music) in Title used as subject

w.label: has Arranged statement (for music) in Title used as subject
w.description: The statement that a musical work is an arrangement.
